Supervised by Dr. Pablo Lyle.
Resected synchronous colon adenocarcinoma.

[end section id="20102"]

[start section id="20103"]

Mr. Wedgeworth is a very pleasant 66 year-old male from New York Washington.  He has a prior history significant for colon polyps noted in 1995 but otherwise has no significant past medical history.
#1  April 2010 - Evaluated in a local emergency room after an episode of flu-like symptoms and abdominal pain and a syncopal episode.  Noted to be anemic with a hemoglobin of 6.8.
#2  April 2, 2010 - Colonoscopy performed showing an ulcerated cecal mass.  Biopsies confirmed adenocarcinoma as well as a descending colon mass.  Biopsies indeterminate and numerous other hyperplastic and low dysplastic colon polyps.  EGD negative.  CEA 3.7.  CT-scan showing indeterminate subcentimeter liver lesion.  Chest x-ray negative.
#3  May 4, 2010 - Abdominal ultrasound identifying hepatic cyst only, no evidence of distant metastasis.
#4  May 10, 2010 - Taken by Dr. Ahmad for a subtotal colectomy, ileosigmoid ostomy.  Per operative note, no distant metastasis seen.  Surgical pathology not currently available at this time of dictation.
Mr. Wedgeworth is continuing to recover from surgery and is currently up sitting in bed during our consultation today.

[end section id="20103"]

